Status: Production Reference
Last Updated: 2025-10-21
Source: Official GPT-5 API Documentation

‚úÖ CORRECTED GPT-5 REQUEST STRUCTURE
Based on the official documentation you provided, here's the accurate API structure:
Required Fields
typescript{
  model: "gpt-5",
  
  // ONE OF THESE (not both):
  input: "single string prompt"     // Simple use case
  // OR
  messages: [                       // Chat-based (preferred)
    { role: "system", content: "..." },
    { role: "user", content: "..." }
  ]
}
Optional Parameters
typescript{
  parameters: {
    max_output_tokens: 2000,        // Max response length
    verbosity: "low" | "medium" | "high",
    reasoning_effort: "minimal" | "low" | "medium" | "high"
  },
  
  tools: [                          // External tool definitions
    {
      name: "tool_name",
      type: "custom",
      description: "What this tool does",
      parameters: { ... }
    }
  ]
}

üö® KEY CORRECTIONS FROM MY MISTAKES
Mistake #1: Temperature Parameter
‚ùå What I said: "GPT-5 only supports temperature=1"
‚úÖ Reality: GPT-5 does NOT support temperature at all - removed entirely
Mistake #2: Parameters Location
‚ùå What I showed:
typescript{
  model: "gpt-5",
  messages: [...],
  reasoning_effort: "medium"  // WRONG - flat structure
}
‚úÖ Correct:
typescript{
  model: "gpt-5",
  messages: [...],
  parameters: {                // Nested under "parameters"
    reasoning_effort: "medium"
  }
}
Mistake #3: Token Limits
‚ùå What I said: max_completion_tokens
‚úÖ Correct: max_output_tokens (different parameter name)
Mistake #4: Response Format
‚ùå What I said: JSON Schema goes in response_format
‚ö†Ô∏è Reality: Need to verify if GPT-5 supports response_format or if it uses tools for structured output
